station

Class Slot

  • java.lang.Object
    • station.Slot

  • public class Slot
extends java.lang.Object
    A class representing parking slots. When a Slot is created, it has a unique ID, is online and has no Bike.

    Chloé

    • Method Detail

      • indexSlotState

        public int indexSlotState(java.time.LocalDateTime t)
                   throws NoSlotStateAtDateException
        This method allows to find the SlotState of a Slot at a certain time t, using its index in the SlotHistory list.
        If t is during a SlotState, this SlotState will be returned.
        If t is at a changing time of SlotState, then the SlotState that starts at t will be returned.
        If t is before the first SlotState, it means the Slot was not created at that time, it will throw an exception.
        If t is after the beginning of the current SlotState, the current SlotState will be returned.
        Parameters:
        t -
        Returns:
        index of SlotState of time t in the SlotHistory
        Throws:
        NoSlotStateAtDateException
